# Build artifacts must never enter the build context: COPY would overlay them on top of the
# container's clean restore, and `dotnet publish --no-restore` then chokes on the host's
# project.assets.json (foreign paths). This is why a local `docker build` failed while CI
# (clean checkout, no bin/obj) succeeded.
**/bin/
**/obj/

# Noise that doesn't belong in the image build context.
**/.vs/
.git/
.github/
.claude/
**/*.user
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
